HEADWORD: falcon-gentle
<hw>falcon-gentle</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>faucon-gentil</ets>. See
<er>Falcon</er>, and <er>Genteel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>any female falcon;</def> <specif>especially
--</specif>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>


<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>a female peregrine falcon
(<spn>Falco peregrinus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> falcon-gentil.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The female or young of the
goshawk (<spn>Accipiter gentilis</spn>, formerly <spn>Astur
palumbarius</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Falconine</ent>⟦br⟧
